Team -

Randy is correct. We need to be careful here. If you recall, the pricing that we provided to
Shift4 was predicated upon them moving at least 50% of their enterprise business that they
currently run on First Data over to us. This represents more than 120 of their enterprise level
clients. They also agreed to move any brand new enterprise deals that they signed going forward
to us. At the point that they submitted the pricing request to us through Randy, we believed that
we had an agreement with Shift4 regarding enterprise business. As such, we provided very
aggressive pricing in that area. (This impacted our basis in interchange by 3-4 basis points.
Based on an estimated $400 million in volume, this equates to roughly $150,000 in profit to
CardConnect.)

As everyone is now well aware, the enterprise piece never materialized. In multiple
conversations that I had directly with JD, he confirmed their intention to move forward as per our
original discussions. It is important to note that Shift4 is realizing a massive windfall on the backs of
the CardConnect shareholders because we executed our deal with the understanding that the
enterprise clients were imminent.

All of this said, I am obviously very sensitive to their importance as a strategic partner and our
desire to grow that relationship. Therefore, the pricing request in question MUST be considered in
the full context of the overall relationship, not just this one cherry picked opportunity that they are
bringing forward.

Thank you.

J.D.
